Informatics as a profession, its role in the society, studying it, its history  and different directions of scientific study.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To give a general overview of the role of informatics in the society and the jobs related to it. To give an overview of Computer Science, including its history and its main disciplines. To motivate students in their further studies in the field of informatics.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student can: 1. describe different informatics-related professions, what they entail and what their importance is in the society. 2. reflect on the reasons he has for studying this and the other informatics-related subjects 3. bring out the main events in the history of informatics and explain their importance 4. give an overview of the different disciplines in computer science or describe some of their more important aspects.
